---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-16">
    <section class="relative py-32 md:py-44 wood-texture overflow-hidden">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 relative z-10">
        <span class="text-brand-gold text-xs tracking-[0.32em] uppercase">About TIMBRCase</span>
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl mt-5 mb-14 leading-[1.05]">
          From the bench<br/>
          <span class="italic text-brand-gold">to your desk.</span>
        </h1>

        <div class="space-y-7 text-brand-cream/85 text-lg md:text-xl leading-[1.75] font-light">
          <p>
            TIMBRCase began with a simple belief: a computer doesn't have to look like one. Most cases are built to be hidden — black boxes pushed under a desk. We think the object you spend hours next to should feel as considered as the desk itself.
          </p>
          <p>
            So we make them slowly. The birch comes from a family-run timber supplier here in Europe. The panels are laser-cut by a specialist with more than twenty years on the same machines. Everything else — bonding, sanding, finishing, mounting, testing — happens in one small workshop in Germany, close to the river Rhine.
          </p>
          <p>
            We work in small batches because that's the only way to keep the standard high and the price fair. No assembly line, no mystery factory, no rushing a piece of wood that needs another hour with the sandpaper.
          </p>
          <p>
            Behind it all is a long love affair with two crafts: building PCs — for ourselves, family, friends, anyone who ever asked — and, for many years, building loudspeakers. Two worlds where wood and electronics quietly belong together. TIMBRCase is what happens when you stop keeping them apart.
          </p>
          <p class="pt-6">
            <span class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-brand-cream not-italic leading-snug block">
              Sourced in Europe. Built by hand. Made to live in the room with you.
            </span>
          </p>

          <div class="pt-10">
            <a href="/#reserve" class="inline-block px-7 py-3.5 rounded-full bg-brand-purple text-brand-cream font-semibold hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
              Choose Your TIMBRCase →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
